The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 13 December is 10,500 (1,215.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 08 December, there were 699 new confirmed cases (80.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 01 December, there were 488 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 43% (211 extra cases).
